</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBF2F3FFF9D306EFF75EFB94E3011C4" blockId="22.[188,1399,1008,1176]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">
<taxonomicName id="4C0054BCFF9D306EFF75EFB94DCC1156" authority="Ranasinghe &amp; Eberle &amp; Athukorala &amp; Benjamin &amp; Ahrens, 2022" authorityName="Ranasinghe &amp; Eberle &amp; Athukorala &amp; Benjamin &amp; Ahrens" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,432,1008,1034]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Maladera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hiyarensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B974F32DFF9D306EFF75EFB94DCC1156" box="[189,432,1008,1034]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">Maladera hiyarensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2474E56FF9D306EFE7DEFB84E6C1157" box="[437,528,1009,1035]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is in external appearance similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0054BCFF9D306EFC7CEFB8490B1157" authority="Fabrizi &amp; Ahrens, 2014" authorityName="Fabrizi &amp; Ahrens" authorityYear="2014" box="[948,1399,1008,1035]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Maladera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anderssoni">
<emphasis id="B974F32DFF9D306EFC7CEFB848201156" box="[948,1116,1008,1034]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">M. anderssoni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9152CEFF9D306EFBABEFB9490B1157" author="Fabrizi S. &amp; Ahrens D." box="[1123,1399,1008,1035]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" pagination="1 - 124" refId="ref31831" refString="Fabrizi S. &amp; Ahrens D. 2014. A monograph of the Sericini of Sri Lanka (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae). Bonn Zoological Bulletin, Supplements 61: 1 - 124." type="journal article" year="2014">Fabrizi &amp; Ahrens, 2014</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0054BCFF9D306EFF38E85D4EE71172" authority="Fabrizi &amp; Ahrens, 2014" authorityName="Fabrizi &amp; Ahrens" authorityYear="2014" box="[240,667,1043,1070]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Maladera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="romanoi">
<emphasis id="B974F32DFF9D306EFF38E85D4D061171" box="[240,378,1044,1069]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">M. romanoi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9152CEFF9D306EFE4BE85A4EE71172" author="Fabrizi S. &amp; Ahrens D." box="[387,667,1043,1070]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" pagination="1 - 124" refId="ref31831" refString="Fabrizi S. &amp; Ahrens D. 2014. A monograph of the Sericini of Sri Lanka (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae). Bonn Zoological Bulletin, Supplements 61: 1 - 124." type="journal article" year="2014">Fabrizi &amp; Ahrens, 2014</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
being, however, stouter in shape and larger, the aedeagus has the distal part longer and narrower. The aedeagus is also rather similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0054BCFF9D306EFBAAE8714D221128" authority="Fabrizi &amp; Ahrens, 2014" authorityName="Fabrizi &amp; Ahrens" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Maladera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="badullana">
<emphasis id="B974F32DFF9D306EFBAAE8714883110D" box="[1122,1279,1079,1105]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">M. badullana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9152CEFF9D306EFACDE87E4D221128" author="Fabrizi S. &amp; Ahrens D." pageId="22" pageNumber="79" pagination="1 - 124" refId="ref31831" refString="Fabrizi S. &amp; Ahrens D. 2014. A monograph of the Sericini of Sri Lanka (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae). Bonn Zoological Bulletin, Supplements 61: 1 - 124." type="journal article" year="2014">Fabrizi &amp; Ahrens, 2014</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but the ventral convexity is in this new species less pronounced and the distal portion is longer and reflexed (lateral view).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31A7CB4FF9D306EFF75E8F649641054" box="[189,1304,1215,1288]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" type="etymology">
