<heading id="D0F79853FF9D306EFF75E8F64D381185" bold="true" box="[189,324,1215,1241]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B974F32DFF9D306EFF75E8F64D381185" bold="true" box="[189,324,1215,1241]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBF2F3FFF9D306EFF75E8A449641054" blockId="22.[189,1304,1261,1288]" box="[189,1304,1261,1288]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">
The new species is named after its 
<typeStatus id="54BB919DFF9D306EFD9FE8A74EF61054" box="[599,650,1262,1288]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">type</typeStatus>
locality ‘Hiyare’ (adjective in the nominative singular).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
